Package: gwasurvivr
Type: Package
Title: gwasurvivr: an R package for genome wide survival analysis
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Abbas", "Rizvi", email = "aarizv@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Ezgi", "Karaesmen", role = "aut"),
    person("Martin", "Morgan", role = "aut"),
    person("Lara", "Sucheston-Campbell", role = "aut"))
Description: gwasurvivr performs genome-wide survival analysis by fitting Cox
    proportional hazard models to imputed genetic data. For speed it calls the
    survival package's per-variant fitter directly, warm-started from a
    covariate-only fit, and processes variants in parallel chunks. It reads
    VCF (Michigan/Minimac and Sanger imputation servers), PLINK, IMPUTE2 and
    GDS inputs.
